  "decision_conditions": [
    "Occupier",
    "The development must be begun not later than the expiration of three years beginning with the date hereof.\r\rReason: To comply with Section 91 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990, as amended.",
    "All external facing materials, treatments and finishes shall be similar to those of the original building and maintained and retained thereafter. This applies unless differences are shown on the drawings we have approved. \r\rReason: To ensure that the extension harmonises with the existing building and to ensure compliance with Policy 28 of the Sutton Local Plan 2018.",
    "The development must be carried out in accordance with the provisions of the Fire Safety Statement by Azen Architects.\r\rReason: To ensure that the development incorporates the necessary fire safety measures in accordance with the Mayor's London Plan Policy D12.",
    "The development hereby approved shall be constructed in accordance with the approved Flood Risk Statement .01) prepared by Azen Architects Ltd and dated May 2025. Prior to first occupation, written confirmation that the recommended flood\rresistance and resilience measures, have been implemented as part of the of the outbuilding as built must be submitted to the Local Planning Authority and approved in writing. All of the approved measures must thereafter be retained for as long as the development is in existence.\r\rReason: To comply with Policy 31 of the Sutton Local Plan 2018.",
    "The outbuilding hereby permitted shall be only used for purposes ancillary and incidental to the main dwelling and for no other purposes. It shall not be occupied at any time other than for purposes ancillary to the residential use of the dwelling known as 1 River Gardens. It shall at no time be used as a separate residential unit. To ensure the ancillary nature of the outbuilding it shall at no time have;\ri) a separate postal address, \rii) Its own kitchen or cooking facilities when a bathroom or WC is also present.\riii) separate metres for the provision of services,\riv) a separate and registered Land Registry title,\rv) a separate Council tax account,\rvi) a separate access independent of the main dwelling house.\r\rReason:  To ensure the ancillary nature of the outbuilding hereby permitted is not used as a separate unit of residential accommodation or for purposes other than that incidental to the enjoyment of the main dwellinghouse in accordance with policy 9 and 29 of the Sutton Local Plan."
  ],
